{%- comment -%}
  Proportional page scaling for large monitors — the "VW fix" agreed at the
  08.07 meeting. The client's test: browser zoom at 200% on a big monitor
  makes the site look right ("пропорционално сайта изглежда по същия начин").
  This reproduces exactly that: at or below the 1920px reference width the
  page is untouched; on wider screens the whole page zooms uniformly, so
  layout, spacing and positioning stay identical — just scaled to the screen.
  Covers every section (khan + stock) without touching individual px values.
{%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  body { zoom: var(--khan-page-zoom, 1); }
</style>
<script>
  (function () {
    var REF = 1920;
    function apply() {
      var w = document.documentElement.clientWidth || window.innerWidth;
      document.documentElement.style.setProperty(
        '--khan-page-zoom',
        w > REF ? (w / REF).toFixed(4) : '1'
      );
    }
    apply();
    window.addEventListener('resize', apply);
    window.addEventListener('orientationchange', apply);
  })();
</script>
